  "intermediate_belief": "If I can't even focus on simple tasks I planned, it means I'm failing and there's no point in trying. If I let myself down, others will see me as incapable and unworthy. I have to be productive to prove I'm not useless.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I can't get myself to do anything, it proves that I'm hopeless and things will never get better. If I keep failing to follow through, it means I'll always be stuck like this.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client tends to avoid distressing feelings and thoughts by withdrawing from planned activities and engaging in passive distraction, such as watching television. This avoidance provides temporary relief but reinforces feelings of helplessness and disengagement. There is a pattern of rumination and negative self-talk that maintains the depressive cycle.",
  "situation": "Planned a weekend for sewing and catching up on work tasks. Was unable to focus on familiar tasks and spent the day watching television.",
